==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle French ''[[turbant]]'', from Italian ''[[turbante]]'', from Turkish ''[[tülbent]]'', from Persian ''[[dulband]]''.
===Pronounciation===
*[[Pronunciation guide|IPA]]: /ˈtɜːrbən/
===Noun===
{{en-noun|turban|turbans}}

#[[Category:Clothing]] Man's [[head-dress]] made by [[wind]]ing a [[length]] of [[cloth]] round the head.
#[[Category:Clothing]] Woman's close-fitting [[hat]] with little or no [[brim]].

